Oscar nominations and victories increase film earnings, and studios woo academy  
members' votes. The Irving Thalberg award is useful for acknowledging overlooked 
giants. Steven Spielberg received it in 1987. Spike Lee blamed the few "Do the Right 
Thing" nominations on generational politics and racism. Oscar shows have been 
criticized for their excesses. Disney sued when the 1989 program opened with an 
unauthorized Snow White routine. The academy sued when other awards resembled the 
Oscar too closely, but a federal judge ruled the statuette was not copyrighted. The 
academy has tried to block Oscar sales. The gold-plated, 8-pound, 13-inch Oscar is 
manufactured by Chicago's R.S. Owens Co.</SUM> 
